About the job
Join the Digital Experience & Marketing team to help manage one of Australia’s largest and most complex web presences. With over a million public webpages and a weekly traffic volume exceeding one million sessions, this role is critical to maintaining a world-class digital experience.

As a CMS Developer, you will focus on the continual improvement of web publishing platforms.

You will bridge the gap between technical implementation and stakeholder needs, ensuring the platform remains scalable, user-friendly, and aligned with modern digital standards.

Key Responsibilities
Platform Development: Lead the technical implementation of new CMS functionality, components, and templates.
Digital Excellence: Design and configure system improvements to handle significant scale while upholding technical excellence.
Strategic Collaboration: Act as an expert advisor to stakeholders on leveraging CMS page templates to achieve communication goals.
Agile Integration: Participate in daily agile rituals, contributing to product innovation from ideation through to implementation.
Continuous Optimisation: Use platform data and emerging tech trends to optimize workflows and system performance.
Documentation: Maintain essential change logs and technical documentation to support a high-performing web community. 
